26/06/2006
TEHRAN, Iran -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul arrived in Tehran on Saturday (24 June) for talks aimed at overcoming the standoff over Iran's nuclear programme. Before leaving Ankara, he told reporters that he was carrying a message from Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan, urging Tehran to co-operate with the international community. "Turkey believes a diplomatic resolution of this issue can help maintain stability in the region," Gul said. (AP - 25/06/06) 
